Mpho Raborife, News24 (iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg -&nbsp;A Lebanese man was caught in possession of gold bars worth about R7m, at OR Tambo International Airport, the SA Revenue Service said on Monday.The man was en route to Dubai when customs officials found 17 bars and three discs of gold in his black leather bag on Sunday, spokesperson Sandile Memela said.The man was allegedly trying to leave the country without proper documentation and allegedly had self-generated invoices, Memela said.He was handed over to police.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.